title: Transporter-2 Mission
description:
On Wednesday, June 30 at 3:31 p.m. EDT, Falcon 9 launched the Transporter-2, SpaceXâ€™s second dedicated SmallSat Rideshare Program mission, from Space Launch Complex 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida. The mission also marked SpaceXâ€™s second launch to a polar orbit from Florida. This was the eighth launch and landing of this Falcon 9 first stage booster in exactly one year, which previously supported launch of GPS III Space Vehicle 03, Turksat 5A, and five Starlink missions. Following stage separation, SpaceX landed Falcon 9â€™s first stage on Landing Zone 1 (LZ-1) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station.

On board this launch were 85 commercial and government spacecraft (including CubeSats, microsats, and orbital transfer vehicles) and 3 Starlink satellites. While there were fewer spacecraft on board compared to Transporter-1, this mission launched more mass to orbit for SpaceXâ€™s customers.

title: I Survived 5000 Days in Hardcore Minecraft - The Movie
description:
After 13 months I've hit day 5000 in my Hardcore world that I stream every day of the week except for Mondays, right here on YT. 
I've only slept in the world for around 60 times, putting my playtime at over 69 irl days. It's been a grind but also a magical journey. In this video I take you with me on that journey from 4000-5000 days.
 
This past year we had a lockdown, Dream SMP, Origins SMP and Hermitcraft were all amazing. Dream, TommyInnit and TechnoBlade became superstars. We all watched Minecraft Manhunt all the time while Luke TheNotable, Forge Labs and everyone survived 100 days in everything. It's all Minecraft but in my case it was one continuous grind.
